  "prompt": "Where can I update the latest FIFA squad 14 for PC offline?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, FIFA 14 is an older title, and EA Sports no longer supports it with official updates. However, there are community-driven options to update the squads offline for PC. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### 1. **Community Mods and Patches**\n   - Websites like **ModdingWay**, **FIFA Infinity**, or **Soccergaming** often host fan-made updates and mods for older FIFA games, including FIFA 14.\n   - Look for a squad update or patch that matches your version of the game (e.g., the latest squads for the 2023/2024 season).\n   - Download the mod or patch and follow the installation instructions provided by the mod creators.\n\n### 2. **Manual Squad Updates**\n   - Some community tools allow you to manually edit squads, players, and transfers using in-game editors or external tools like **DB Master** or **Creation Master**.\n   - These tools require some technical knowledge but can be used to update squads offline.\n\n### 3. **Check Gaming Forums**\n   - Forums like **Reddit** (e.g., r/FIFA or r/FIFAmodding) or **Soccergaming** often have active communities sharing updated squad files.\n\n### Important Notes:\n   - Always back up your game files before installing any mods or patches.\n   - Ensure that the mods or patches you download are compatible with your version of FIFA 14.\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for the most recent official updates, you\u2019ll need to switch to a newer FIFA title, as EA no longer supports FIFA 14.",
